  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this project is to develop a patient-centered decision aid for decision-making
      about end-stage heart failure treatment. This study seeks to create a decision aid that
      presents outcomes, risks, projected experiences, and uncertainties about Left Ventricular
      Assist Device (LVAD) placement to help patients make values-based decisions about placement.
      The investigators propose a mixed methods design involving a literature search of clinical
      evidence, semi-structured patient interviews, and quantitative data from a multi-site trial
      of patients receiving the decision aid compared to patients not receiving the aid.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
